00:30:50.819 --> 00:30:52.500
so that they can create

00:30:52.500 --> 00:30:53.699
and publish products

00:30:53.699 --> 00:30:54.819
via RStudio Connect

00:30:54.819 --> 00:30:56.180
using both R and Python

00:30:57.540 --> 00:30:58.979
to share with their internal clients

00:30:58.979 --> 00:30:59.859
and stakeholders

00:30:59.859 --> 00:31:01.619
as third reviewer shows here.

00:31:05.140 --> 00:31:06.579
Now we've talked a lot

00:31:06.579 --> 00:31:08.819
along the way about our pro products

00:31:08.819 --> 00:31:09.859
but I want to emphasize

00:31:09.859 --> 00:31:11.140
that our core mission

00:31:11.140 --> 00:31:13.140
is to engage and support

00:31:13.140 --> 00:31:14.660
the R and Python community

00:31:14.660 --> 00:31:16.420
and we do that in a number of different ways.

00:31:17.699 --> 00:31:18.979
The most important of course

00:31:18.979 --> 00:31:21.060
is creating the open source software

00:31:21.060 --> 00:31:24.579
that our users use every week

00:31:25.459 --> 00:31:27.459
but there are a number of different ways we do it.

00:31:27.459 --> 00:31:30.180
We support the RStudio community site

00:31:30.180 --> 00:31:32.339
allowing R users and Python users

00:31:32.339 --> 00:31:34.180
to gather and ask each other questions

00:31:34.180 --> 00:31:36.020
and get answers to those questions.

00:31:36.020 --> 00:31:37.060
That's a great resource.

00:31:37.939 --> 00:31:39.380
We do our annual conference.

00:31:40.260 --> 00:31:42.420
This year it was a virtual conference

00:31:42.420 --> 00:31:43.619
under current circumstances

00:31:43.619 --> 00:31:45.219
but that was just a couple weeks ago

00:31:45.939 --> 00:31:48.260
and we were very gratified

00:31:48.260 --> 00:31:49.300
by the engagement there.

00:31:50.260 --> 00:31:51.300
Check out our blog

00:31:51.300 --> 00:31:53.380
and there's a link there

00:31:53.380 --> 00:31:54.739
to all the globals,

00:31:54.739 --> 00:31:55.939
all sorry, all the videos

00:31:55.939 --> 00:31:57.060
from RStudio Global.

00:31:57.859 --> 00:31:58.819
Many different speakers

00:31:58.819 --> 00:31:59.939
from all around the world.

00:31:59.939 --> 00:32:01.699
Those are all free to watch.

00:32:01.699 --> 00:32:02.979
We had a tremendous amount

00:32:02.979 --> 00:32:03.939
of positive feedback

00:32:03.939 --> 00:32:05.619
both directly on social media

00:32:05.619 --> 00:32:06.579
on that conference

00:32:06.579 --> 00:32:07.219
so I encourage you

00:32:07.219 --> 00:32:08.339
to check out those videos.

00:32:09.219 --> 00:32:10.660
Our education team

00:32:10.660 --> 00:32:12.819
is focused to help

00:32:12.819 --> 00:32:14.339
support the education of R.

00:32:14.339 --> 00:32:15.939
We do a lot of train

00:32:15.939 --> 00:32:17.380
the trainer capabilities

00:32:17.380 --> 00:32:19.619
providing training materials, etc.

00:32:19.619 --> 00:32:21.140
So if you're interested

00:32:21.140 --> 00:32:23.619
in being a certified RStudio R trainer

00:32:23.619 --> 00:32:24.900
check out our education page.

00:32:26.260 --> 00:32:27.300
We're also supporters

00:32:27.300 --> 00:32:28.979
of the R Consortium

00:32:29.780 --> 00:32:31.219
a multi-vendor group

00:32:32.099 --> 00:32:33.699
to support and advance

00:32:33.699 --> 00:32:34.579
the infrastructure

00:32:34.579 --> 00:32:35.540
around the R language

00:32:36.180 --> 00:32:38.099
as well as a platinum sponsor

00:32:38.099 --> 00:32:39.060
of NumFocus

00:32:39.060 --> 00:32:41.300
which provides a tremendous support

00:32:41.300 --> 00:32:42.660
for the Python ecosystem

00:32:42.660 --> 00:32:43.619
among other projects.

00:32:45.060 --> 00:32:46.979
And then finally Ursa Labs.

00:32:46.979 --> 00:32:48.339
We've been a supporter

00:32:48.339 --> 00:32:50.099
of Ursa Labs from the beginning

00:32:50.099 --> 00:32:51.540
and Ursa Labs is devoted

00:32:51.540 --> 00:32:53.939
to developing cross-language capabilities

00:32:53.939 --> 00:32:57.699
such as using the Apache Aero project

00:32:57.699 --> 00:32:59.780
to provide access

00:32:59.780 --> 00:33:01.540
both within R and Python

00:33:01.540 --> 00:33:02.579
to those capabilities.

00:33:05.939 --> 00:33:08.739
And it's important to emphasize

00:33:08.739 --> 00:33:09.859
how our open source

00:33:09.859 --> 00:33:11.859
and pro products tie together.

00:33:11.859 --> 00:33:13.140
Of course, it's our core mission

00:33:13.140 --> 00:33:14.739
as I said to contribute

00:33:14.739 --> 00:33:15.699
open source software

00:33:15.699 --> 00:33:16.420
to the community.

00:33:16.979 --> 00:33:18.099
And we spend over half

00:33:18.099 --> 00:33:19.459
of our engineering resources

00:33:19.459 --> 00:33:20.420
creating this free

00:33:20.420 --> 00:33:21.540
and open source software.

00:33:23.459 --> 00:33:24.900
As the data science community

00:33:24.900 --> 00:33:26.660
adopts open source software

00:33:26.660 --> 00:33:28.099
this drives adoption

00:33:28.099 --> 00:33:30.339
within larger enterprises

00:33:31.140 --> 00:33:32.339
and commercial customers.

00:33:33.540 --> 00:33:34.739
These commercial customers

00:33:34.739 --> 00:33:37.219
in turn buy our pro products

00:33:38.099 --> 00:33:40.099
that are focused on helping scale out

00:33:40.099 --> 00:33:41.300
and operationalize

00:33:41.300 --> 00:33:42.500
open source data science.

00:33:43.300 --> 00:33:45.219
And by buying our pro products

00:33:45.219 --> 00:33:46.579
that provides RStudio

00:33:46.739 --> 00:33:48.660
the funds so that we can sustain

00:33:48.660 --> 00:33:50.420
our ongoing open source work.

00:33:51.060 --> 00:33:52.020
We call this idea

00:33:52.020 --> 00:33:53.219
the virtuous cycle.

00:33:53.219 --> 00:33:54.819
This idea that we're supporting

00:33:54.819 --> 00:33:57.060
our mission to deliver

00:33:57.060 --> 00:33:58.099
free and open source software

00:33:58.099 --> 00:33:59.140
to the community

00:33:59.140 --> 00:34:00.979
by selling the pro software

00:34:00.979 --> 00:34:02.260
to the enterprise companies

00:34:02.260 --> 00:34:03.859
that need those features.

